,type:"SHIELD",weight:6,ac_base:2,content:"*Requires attunement.* This shield provides tremorsense in a 60 ft. radius when held touching the ground."}],armor_enchantments:[{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"Bone Devil",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor grants resistance to bludgeoning, slashing and piercing damage from weapons that aren't silvered. This property works only in the Nine Hells."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"Forest Camo",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor grants advantage to Stealth checks in forrested terrain."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"of Cold and Fire Resistance",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor grants resistance to cold and fire damage."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"of Damage Resistance",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor grants resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from nonmagical attacks."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"of Magic Resistance",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor grants advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"of Stony Camo",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor gives advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made to hide in rocky terrain."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"of the Hydra",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor allows the wearer to ignore harsh terrain in water invironments."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"of the Manticore",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor grants advantage on Animal Handling checks made to tame griffons and wyverns."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"of Winter",content:"*Requires attunement.* This armor grants resistance to cold damage and advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made to hide in snowy terrain."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"Tattered",content:"Must be mended before use."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"Unicorn",content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this armor has advantage against Charm or other mind control effects. Once per day, the wearer can choose to heal themselves for 2d8+2 points. This also removes all diseases and neutralizes all poisons affecting the wearer. This property can't be used again until the next dawn."},{category:"armor_enchantments",name:"Worg",content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this armor has advantage on Persuasion checks on goblins or hobgoblins."}],potions:[{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Guardian Naga Heart",weight:.5,content:"When consumed, Used as a Potion of Vitality."},{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Kraken Ink",weight:0,content:"Used as an Oil of Slipperiness."},{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Potion of Mind Shielding",weight:0,content:"After drinking this potion, you have immunity to Charm and other mind control effects for 1 hour."},{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Potion of Polymorph",weight:0,content:"After drinking this potion, you can effect of a Polymorph spell on the drinker. The effect lasts for 1 hour."},{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Potion of Regeneration",weight:0,content:"The creature that drinks this potion stimulates its own natural Healing ability. They regain 4d8 + 15 Hit Points. For one munute, the target regains 1 hit point at the start of each of its turns (10 h⁠it points each minute).\n\nThe drinker's severed body Members (fingers, legs, tails, and so on), if any, are restored after 2 minutes. If they have the severed part and hold it to the stump, the potion instantaneously causes the limb to knit to the stump."},{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Potion of the Path",weight:0,content:"After drinking this potion, you can perfectly recall every route they have taken within the past 8 hours, and automatically succeed on ability checks made to escape a maze or similar areas."},{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Spirit Naga Heart",weight:.5,content:"When consumed, Used as a Potion of Vitality."},{category:"potions",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Tarrasque Blood",weight:.5,content:"Used as a Potion of Supreme Healing.",heal_dice:8,heal_die:"d4",heal_bonus:8}],poisons:[{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Ectoplasmic Poison",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:15,attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d6",damage_type:"necrotic",content:"A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or take 2d6 necrotic damage. The poisoned creature fades between the Material Plane and the Etherial Plane for the next 12 hours. Each attempt to use hold or touch an object requires the creature to roll a d20: On 1-12 the creature is on the Material Plane. On 13-20 they are on the Etherial Plane. When the effect wears off, the creature is returned to the plane on which they were poisoned."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Ettercap Poison",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:11,content:"Target must succeed on a DC 11 Constitution saving throw or be poisoned for 1 minute. The creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Giant Centipede Poison",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:11,attack_damage_dice:3,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must succeed on a DC 11 Constitution saving throw or take 10 (3d6) poison damage. If the poison damage reduces the target to 0 hit points, the target is stable but poisoned for 1 hour, even after regaining hit points, and is paralyzed while poisoned in this way."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Giant Scorpion Poison",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:12,attack_damage_dice:4,attack_damage_die:"d10",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw, taking 22 (4d10) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Giant Spider Venom",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:11,attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d8",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must make a DC 11 Constitution saving throw, taking 9 (2d8) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If the poison damage reduces the target to 0 hit points, the target is stable but poisoned for 1 hour, even after regaining hit points, and is paralyzed while poisoned in this way."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Giant Wasp Poison",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:11,attack_damage_dice:3,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must make a DC 11 Constitution saving throw, taking 10 (3d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If the poison damage reduces the target to 0 hit points, the target is stable but poisoned for 1 hour, even after regaining hit points, and is paralyzed while poisoned in this way."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Giant Wolf Spider Venom",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:11,attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must make a DC 11 Constitution saving throw, taking 7 (2d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If the poison damage reduces the target to 0 hit points, the target is stable but poisoned for 1 hour, even after regaining hit points, and is paralyzed while poisoned in this way."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Phase Spider Venom",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:11,attack_damage_dice:4,attack_damage_die:"d8",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must make a DC 11 Constitution saving throw, taking 18 (4d8) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If the poison damage reduces the target to 0 hit points, the target is stable but poisoned for 1 hour, even after regaining hit points, and is paralyzed while poisoned in this way."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Poisonous Snake Venom",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:10,attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d4",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw, taking 5 (2d4) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Pseudodragon Poison",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:11,content:"Target must succeed on a DC 11 Constitution saving throw or become poisoned for 1 hour. If the saving throw fails by 5 or more, the target falls unconscious for the same duration, or until it takes damage or another creature uses an action to shake it awake."},{category:"poisons",section:"utility",uses:1,name:"Spirit Naga Poison",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:13,attack_damage_dice:7,attack_damage_die:"d8",attack_damage_type:"poison",content:"Target must make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, taking 31 (7d8) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one."}],adv_gear:[{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Anhkeg Acid",weight:1,section:"offense",attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"acid",range:"20/60 ft.",attack_damage_ability:"0",uses:1,content:"Used as Acid. Can be crafted into a Potent Acid that deals 3d6 acid damage on a hit."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Basilisk Eye",weight:0,section:"utility",uses:1,content:"When held toward a target, can cast Flesh to Stone (DC 12). This consumes the eye."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Black Pudding Pudding",weight:1,section:"offense",attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d8",attack_damage_type:"acid",range:"20/60 ft.",attack_damage_ability:"0",uses:1,content:"Used as an Acid that deals 2d8 acid damage on a hit. Can disolve 1 cubic foot of nonmagical metal or wood when poured on such items or surfaces."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Bugbear Tusk",weight:1,content:"Grants advantage on Intimidation checks made against goblinoids when held or worn outwardly."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Demon Ichor",weight:1,section:"offense",attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"acid",range:"20/60 ft.",attack_damage_ability:"0",uses:1,content:"Used as Acid."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Dragon Head",weight:25,recharge:"LONG_REST",uses:1,content:"Requires attunement. When attuned, Used to cast Fireball (save DC 15) once per day from the head."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Ettercap Silk Gland",weight:2,section:"offense",range:"30/60 ft.",saving_throw_vs_ability:"STRENGTH",saving_throw_dc:11,uses:"1d3+2",content:"Used to shoot webbing at a 30/60 ft. range. Larger or smaller creatures only. On a hit, the creature is restrained by webbing. As an action, the restrained creature can make a DC 11 Strength check, escaping from the webbing on a success. The effect ends if the webbing is destroyed. It has AC 10, 5 hit points, is vulnerable to fire damage and immune to bludgeoning, poison and psychic damage. Contains enough silk for 1d3+2 uses."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Gelatinous Cube Residue",weight:1,section:"offense",attack_damage_dice:3,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"acid",range:"20/60 ft.",attack_damage_ability:"0",uses:1,content:"Used as Acid, but deals 3d6 acid damage on a hit."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Giant Fire Beetle Gland",weight:1,section:"utility",content:"Used as a light source. Will continue to glow for 1d6 days after death, providing bright light in a 10 ft. radius and dim light for an additional 10 ft."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Gibbering Mouther Spittle",weight:1,section:"utility",content:"Can be thrown within range (20/60 ft.) where it explodes in a blinding flash of light on impact. Each creature within 5 feet of the flash must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or be blinded until the end of your next turn."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Gray Ooze Residue",weight:1,section:"offense",attack_damage_dice:2,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"acid",range:"20/60 ft.",attack_damage_ability:"0",uses:1,content:"Used as Acid."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Potent Acid",weight:0,section:"offense",attack_damage_dice:3,attack_damage_die:"d6",attack_damage_type:"acid",range:"20/60 ft.",uses:1,attack_ability:"DEX",attack_damage_ability:"0",content:"As an action, you can splash the contents of this vial onto a creature within 5 feet of you or throw the vial up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating the acid as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 3d6 acid damage."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Rust Monster Antennae",weight:1,saving_throw_vs_ability:"DEXTERITY",saving_throw_dc:11,content:"Used to touch a nonmagical metal objects. If the object isn't being worn or carried, the touch destroys a 1-foot cube of it. If the object is being worn or carried by a creature, the creature can make a DC 11 Dexterity saving throw to avoid being touched. If the object touched is either metal armor or a metal shield being worn or carried, its takes a permanent and cumulative -1 penalty to the AC it offers. Armor reduced to an AC of 10 or a Shield that drops to a +0 bonus is destroyed. If the object touched is a held metal weapon, the weapon takes a permanent and cumulative -1 penalty to damage rolls. If its penalty drops to -5, the weapon is destroyed. Once used, the antenna becomes useless."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Vrock Larynx",weight:0,saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:14,content:"Used like a whistle that emits a horrific screech. Each creature within 20 feet of it that can hear it and that isn't a demon must succeed on a DC 14 Constitution saving throw or be stunned until the end of the user's next turn. Used 1d4+2 times before disentegrating."},{category:"adventuring_gear",name:"Vrock Spore Sac",weight:1,section:"offense",attack_damage_dice:5,attack_damage_die:"d1",attack_damage_type:"poison",range:"20/60 ft.",attack_damage_ability:"0",uses:1,content:"Can be thrown with a range of 20/60 ft. On impact it breaks open, releasing a 15-foot-radius cloud of toxic spore. The spores spread around corners. Each creature in that area must succeed on a DC 14 Constitution saving throw or become poisoned. While poisoned in this way, a target takes 5 (1d10) poison damage at the start of each of its turns. A target can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. Emptying a vial of holy water on the target also ends the effect on it."}],wondrous_items:[{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Amulet of Darkness",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this amulet can cast Darkness in a 15 ft. radius 3 times a day. Darkvision cannot penetrate this darkness, nor natural light illuminate it. If any of the darkness overlaps an area of light created by a spell of 2nd level or lower, the spell creating the light is dispelled."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Amulet of Immutable Form",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this amulet has advantage on all saving throws against effects that would alter the wearer's form."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Amulet of Lightning Absorption",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* If an attack on the wearer of this amulet would inflict lightning damage, it instead heals the wearer for the same amount of points."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Amulet of Luck",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* If the wearer of this amulet fails a saving throw, they can choose to succeed instead. Once this property is used, it cannot be used again until the next dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Amulet of the Harpy",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this amulet has advantage on saving throws against Charm or other mind controlling effects."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Amulet of the Lich",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* This amulet can tether the wearer to the target of its choice withen 30 ft at will. Whenever the wearer takes damage, the target must make a DC 18 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the wearer takes half the damage (rounded down), and the target takes the remaining damage. This tether lasts until initiative count 20 on the next round or until the wearer and the target are no longer within range. Once used, this property can't be used again until the next dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Amulet of the Wraith",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this amulet can create a specter from a humanoid that has died violently within the hour. This specter is under the control of the possessor of the amulet. Once this property is used, it can't be used again until the next dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Antimagic Amulet",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* This amulet grants the wearer advantage on saving throws against spells and magic effects."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Boots of Web Walking",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* These boots allows the wearer to ignore movement restrictions caused by webbing."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Cloak of Fire Resistance",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While you wear this cloak, you have resistance to fire damage."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Cloak of Forest Camo",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While you wear this cloak, you have advantage to Stealth checks in forrested terrain."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Cloak of Stony Camo",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While you wear this cloak, you have advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made to hide in rocky terrain."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Cloak of the Manticore",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While you wear this cloak, you have advantage on Animal Handling checks made to tame griffons and wyverns."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Cloak of Winter",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While you wear this cloak, you have resistance to cold damage and advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made to hide in snowy terrain."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Doppelganger Cloak",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While you wear this cloak, you have advantage on Deception checks when the cloak used as part of a disguise."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Green Hag Nose",weight:1,content:"When worn like a mask, allows the wearer to mimic animal sounds and human voices. A creature that hears the sounds can tell they are imitations with a successful DC 14 Insight check."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Heartstone",weight:0,recharge:"LONG_REST",uses:1,content:"This lustrous black gem allows its possessor to become ethereal. The touch of a heartstone also cures any disease. Once either effect is used, the heartstone can't be used for either purpose until the next dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Helm of Intimidation",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While wearing this helm, you have advantage on intimidation checks."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Helm of Magic Detection",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* While wearing this helm, you can cast Detect Magic as the spell with double the distance. This helm has 3 charges, and regains 1d3 charges at dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Helm of Weather Control",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this helm can cast Control Weather as the spell with no components once per day. This effect cannot be used again until the next dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Lion Head",weight:15,recharge:"LONG_REST",uses:1,content:"Requires attunement. When attuned, Used to cast Fear (save DC 15) once per day from the head."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Medusa Head",weight:15,range:"30 ft.",saving_throw_vs_ability:"CONSTITUTION",saving_throw_dc:14,content:"When a creature that can see the medusa's eyes starts its turn within 30 feet of the medusa, it must make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. If the saving throw fails by 5 or more, the creature is instantly petrified. Otherwise, a creature that fails the save begins to turn to stone and is restrained. The restrained creature must repeat the saving throw at the end of its next turn, becoming petrified on a failure or ending the effect on a success. The petrification lasts until the creature is freed by the greater restoration spell or other magic."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Mummy Lord Head",weight:10,range:"60 ft.",saving_throw_vs_ability:"WISDOM",saving_throw_dc:16,content:"If the target can see the mummy lord head, it must succeed on a DC 16 Wisdom saving throw against this magic or become frightened until the end of the wielder's next turn. If the target fails the saving throw by 5 or more, it is also paralyzed for the same duration. A target that succeeds on the saving throw is immune to the Dreadful Glare of all mummies and mummy lords for the next 24 hours."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Sahuagin Helm",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* grants the effect of a Speak with Animals spell, but only works on sharks. Once used, this property can't be used again until the next dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Shambling Mound Root-Stem",weight:4,content:"When held, provides resistance to lightning damage. Can be crafted into an Amulet of Lightning Absorption. If an attack on the wearer would inflict lightning damage, it instead heals the wearer for the same amouht of points."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Shield Guardian Finger",weight:0,content:"Used like a Ring of Spell Storing but will only hold 1 spell at a time, and only spells of 4th level or lower."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Stone Golem Heart",weight:1,content:"When worn around the neck, Used as an amulet allowing the wearer to cast Slow as the spell with no components (saving throw DC 17)."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Unicorn Cloak",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this cloak has advantage against Charm or other mind control effects. Once per day, the wearer can choose to heal themselves for 2d8+2 points. This also removes all diseases and neutralizes all poisons affecting the wearer. This property can't be used again until the next dawn."},{category:"wondrous_items",name:"Worg Cloak",weight:0,content:"*Requires attunement.* The wearer of this cloak has advantage on Persuasion checks on goblins or hobgoblins."}]})});
